<br>
Personally I have had some of my most fun in EQ dueling folk.  My last duel was my lvl 24 SK versus a lvl 27 rogue in my guild in Karnor's Castle.  The skeleton adds were fun - we'd kill the blasted things then go back to our duel.  He would go stealth mode then make strafing runs at me while I swung wildly at everything and bashed him when he did make contact.  Was a hoot!<br>
<br>
Anyways, I totally agree with the pvp concept on blue servers.  But there has to be rewards for good pvpers and consequences for griefers as has been stated.  Its not like there aren't ways to grief people as it is, ya know.  &quot;OMG they horrified our clerics!!!!&quot;  I think weeding out the griefers could be a nice side benefit to developing the pvp concept fully.<br>
<br>
BTW I remember the monster experiment that they tried very fondly.  I wish they would re-implement that!  Yeah I know it was uber-exploitable, but see my statement above about weeding out the griefers.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vladius>Vladius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/18/03 7:39:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25419.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sam DeathWalker RoXoRs yur BoXoRs!</span><hr size=1> PVP has always been a controversial topic.  It looks as if VI put a lot of thought in the current system.  In the case of a lot of people their first experiance with an MMORPG was loggin onto UO as a n00b, trying to learn the lay of the land and all of a sudden your dead....most left and didn't come back after that.  <br>
<br>
I am still trying to understand the scope of the animosity that I have seen from some of the zek server players and the so clled &quot;carebear&quot; servers.  I have heard it said that the zeks were placed in game to protect the blue servers from those very types of players.  Of course irregardless the griefers will find a way despite the rules.<br>
<br>
I agree that pvp is tied to roleplaying which in all honesty is something this game sorely needs.  There should be a way of rewarding roleplaying in PVP while at the same time punishing those who seek to exploit the system to gain amusement at another's expense.  <br>
<br>
Here are some ideas:<br>
<br>
Faction PVP:  Simply make it legal for you to PVP a opposite alignment person in you own home city.  While playing my SK I would often go through Third Gate and there would usually be a Mage parked in one of the distant mansions killing an NPC.  Under this system just by walking in the zone makes him a target.  This system could be confusing in areas like West Freeport where good and evil alignments can walk safely.<br>
<br>
Zonewide PVP:  This would be great for events.  Instead of leaving your guild to join a guildwar guild.  When the event starts a zonewide message would go across the zone.  If you don't want to get PKed get out.  Some kind of warning could be worked in as well. Wars are fine and good but on a side note they generate way too much lag.<br>
<br>
Controlled Zones:  Similar to the player enforced zones on the Zeks.  Some zones would be labeled good neutral or evil.  Evil would include all the evil cities, Nektulos forest, Feerott.  Would be fun to see all the zones adjoining Cabilis PVP...this would make hunting in Kunark very interesting.  Good zones would be all good cities, Greater Faydark, Qeynos Hills, Butcherblock Mountains, Misty Thicket.  Keep the existing cap on PVP intact though although it would be interesting to see another pvpstandard for those under level 10 that can only attack those under level 10.  In some of the disputed areas you could have battles to determine who controlls the zone, maybe whichever side has the most kills gets control.  <br>
<br>
I personally think the designers should have paid more attention to the cities.  Back in the old days people used to raid cities for fun.  What if there was a quest or item based reason to do so? Only in Velious do you see anything resembling this anymore.  <br>
<br>
 <p>Vladius Solarwind<br>
55th level Evoker of Solusek Ro<br>
